Vol / Page: 123
Edition: 1954
Quote:  The third day, as the sheep mobbed up, it was necessary to exercise great care in running a dog, for a rough turn could cause a bolt, or even a smother, if a deep gut came in the way. ... As soon as the whole mob was in hand and had been given a few turns, the danger of a smother lessened.
